# =============================================================================
# WC_STAGING_API_SECRETS — example reference
# =============================================================================
#
# This file documents the value that should be pasted into the GitHub secret
# named `WC_STAGING_API_SECRETS` (Settings → Secrets and variables → Actions
# → Secrets → New repository secret).
#
# The deploy workflow at .github/workflows/wc-staging-deploy.yml parses this
# value and stores each pair as an Azure Container App secret, injected into
# the running container as `KEY=secretref:<lowercase-hyphenated-key>` so the
# value is encrypted at rest in Azure and never appears in workflow logs.
#
# Format rules (verified against the parser at wc-staging-deploy.yml:85-133):
#   • One KEY=VALUE per line. Blank lines are tolerated.
#   • Values cannot contain leading/trailing whitespace (trimmed by `xargs`
#     during parsing). Internal whitespace inside a value is preserved.
#   • Keep each VALUE on one line — newlines inside a value will split the
#     entry.
#
# DO NOT COMMIT REAL SECRET VALUES TO THIS FILE.
# =============================================================================
#
# === Key-by-key reference (for documentation only — not the paste value) ===
#
#   JWT_SECRET                    32+ char random hex (e.g. `openssl rand -hex 32`)
#   JWT_REFRESH_SECRET            32+ char random hex (different from JWT_SECRET)
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD             staging Postgres password
#   EMAIL_PASS                    SMTP app password for the EMAIL_USER account
#   AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY     Storage account access key (Azure Portal → Storage account → Access keys)
#   GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY         server-side Google Places API key (restrict by IP in GCP Console)
#   REDIS_URL                     full Redis connection URL including password (`rediss://:PASS@HOST:6380` for Azure Cache for Redis with TLS)
#   STRIPE_SECRET_KEY             `sk_test_…` in staging, `sk_live_…` in production
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET         `whsec_…` from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks (main endpoint)
#   STRIPE_CONNECT_WEBHOOK_SECRET `whsec_…` from Stripe Dashboard → Webhooks (Connect-events endpoint)
#
# === WHAT TO PASTE INTO THE GITHUB SECRET ===
# Replace each <…> placeholder with the real staging value, then paste the
# block below as the secret value.

JWT_SECRET=<generate-via-openssl-rand-hex-32>
JWT_REFRESH_SECRET=<generate-via-openssl-rand-hex-32>
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=<staging-db-password>
EMAIL_PASS=<smtp-app-password>
AZURE_STORAGE_ACCOUNT_KEY=<azure-blob-storage-account-key>
GOOGLE_PLACES_API_KEY=<google-places-server-side-api-key>
REDIS_URL=rediss://:<password>@<staging-redis-host>.redis.cache.windows.net:6380
STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
STRIPE_CONNECT_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxx
